The paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for art generation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of computer-generated images and artworks from Vincent van Gogh and Rembrandt van Rijn suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also relevant. The exploration of implications for computational creativity suggests that graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms for training and testing suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) is also relevant.
